# Python Agent Conventions

## LLM Provider (mandatory abstraction)

- All agents use `create_provider()` from `agents/common/llm/` — never import Ollama or Gemini directly in agent logic.
- Switch provider via `LLM_PROVIDER=mock|ollama|gemini` env var.
- Tests use `MockLLMProvider` with deterministic responses.

## Agent Roles

| Package | Role |
|---------|------|
| `client_agent/` | Posts projects, accepts/rejects deliveries, owns budget |
| `manager_agent/` | Negotiates with clients, hires workers, orchestrates and monitors |
| `worker_agent/` | Claims tasks, delivers work, negotiates subcontract pay |

## Agent Communication

- **Only Kafka** for inter-agent and agent-to-platform messaging. No HTTP calls between agents.
- Ledger HTTP is allowed for account bootstrap and escrow operations only.
- Consume: `tasks.posted`, `tasks.claimed`, `tasks.delivered`, `payments.proposed`, `simulation.tick`, `macro.snapshots`.
- Produce: `tasks.claimed`, `tasks.delivered`, `payments.proposed`, `payments.accepted`.

## Code Style

- Type hints on all public functions.
- LangGraph: explicit state graph (observe → decide → act); document nodes in module docstring.
- Structured logging with `correlation_id` from Kafka headers.

## Testing

- `pytest` for every agent decision function.
- No real LLM calls in CI — always mock the provider.
